    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="501"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/538.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to the Dominican
                            Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed that the Haitian Government has dispatched 400 men, artillery, and
                    1000 rifles, to Thomazeau, which the Dominican Government believes to be in aid
                    of the revolutionists, and requests me to ask your assistance in procuring two
                    fast gunboats with good batteries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
